/* ============================================================================
 * ast.iii - Stage-1 .iii port of ast.c (RITCHIE Stage 2.2).
 *
 * Byte-equivalent re-implementation of the C reference ast.c (2849 LOC):
 * the four-pool Merkle DAG, open-addressed hash-cons, position side-table,
 * list / string / annotation arenas, zipper, resumable walk-state, canonical
 * serialiser, and diff.  Mirrors lex.iii's discipline: the opaque container
 * and every node live in malloc'd blocks accessed by byte offset (iiis-0
 * cannot deref C structs natively); heap + byte + SHA-256 come from the
 * generic lex_runtime.c helpers (NIH-clean, already linked into iiis-1; no
 * 7th SHA-256 copy).  All layout constants are offsetof-verified against
 * ast.h / ast_internal.h (CONVERGENCE-AUDIT S2.2).
 *
 * iiis-0 trap discipline (lex_port_audit S4): single-line fn decls, <=4 args,
 * no break/continue (sentinel flags), unsigned u64 ordering only, byte values
 * not char literals, NUL-pool for any returned C-string, ASCII comments with
 * balanced slash-star markers, helpers to stay under the ~8 parser recursion
 * ceiling, malloc+memcpy+free growth (no realloc extern).
 * ============================================================================ */

module ast

/* --- Generic C-side runtime helpers (shared with lex.iii) ---------------- */
